From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
Date: Fri, 6 Mar 2026 23:51:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] rockchip: rk3588: Add support for the OrangePI 5 Pro

Add support for the Xunlong Orange Pi 5 Pro single-board computer,
which is based on the Rockchip RK3588S SoC. The Pro variant
differs from the base Orange Pi 5 in several key hardware areas:

- Ethernet: PCIe-attached (MT YT6801) NIC instead of GMAC1 (RGMII).
  GMAC0 disabled.
- Audio: ES8388 codec on I2C3 / I2S2 (m1 mux) instead of I2C6 / I2S1.
  Now fixed routing, replaced master.
- LEDs: GPIO-driven (blue + green) using PWM.
- Storage: eMMC (SDHCI) enabled by default, plus SD card and SDIO.
  FSPI not enabled by default (Pin conflict with eMMC)
- USB: USB-C is power-delivery only (no FUSB302 / alt-mode); a
  dedicated USB3 Type-A port is provided via usbdp_phy0 lanes 2/3.
- Wireless: AP6256 WiFi/BT module on SDIO + UART9.
- Fan: PWM-controlled with thermal cooling maps.
  Optimized speed to extend System Lifetime.
- 40-pin header: I2C1 and I2C4 exposed for GPIO expansion.
- Video: HDMI0 and DP0 enabled by default.
  DP0 has LT8711UXD_U2 converter USB-DP to HDMI (I2C nc).

The DTS file includes the base rk3588s-orangepi-5.dtsi and applies
the necessary overrides and additions for the Pro hardware.

This patch introduces the basic U-Boot defconfig and syncs the initial
device tree submission from the Linux kernel mailing list.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/linux-rockchip/20260304025521.210377-4-dennis@ausil.us/
Suggested-by: Dennis Gilmore <dennis@ausil.us>
Signed-off-by: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
